&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sponsorship Operations &amp;amp; Fulfillment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the operational planning and execution of all sponsor deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate sponsorship agreements into clear execution plans and timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage booth logistics, sponsor activations, assets collection, and on-site requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary operational point of contact for sponsors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all sponsor benefits are fulfilled accurately and on schedule&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable processes and documentation to support year-over-year growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registration Systems &amp;amp; Attendee Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and manage event registration platforms (example: Cvent, Bizzabo)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and maintain registration flows, ticket structures, and system configurations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee attendee data management, segmentation, reporting, and data accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Marketing to align registration setup with campaign strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on-site registration operations and check-in workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Excell

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Come join the organization that is redefining security for the AI era. As one of the&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.wiz.io/blog/100m-arr-in-18-months-wiz-becomes-the-fastest-growing-software-company-ever&quot;&gt; fastest-growing startups ever,&lt;/a&gt; we enable teams to secure cloud and AI applications by connecting code, cloud, and runtime into a single shared context. Trusted by security teams all over the world, we have a proven&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.g2.com/products/wiz-wiz/reviews&quot;&gt; track record of success&lt;/a&gt; and a culture that values world-class talent. Not to mention, we&#39;re now&lt;a href=&quot;https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/identity-security/google-completes-acquisition-of-wiz&quot;&gt; powered by Google&lt;/a&gt;, meaning we offer our customers an AI-powered platform that harnesses Google’s Threat Intelligence and Security Operations to better detect, prevent, and respond to threats across all environments, allowing for further innovation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Wizards from all over the globe work together to protect the infrastructure of our customers, including over 50% of the Fortune 100, who trust us to scan and secure over 230 billion files daily. We’re honored to be a leading player in a massive and growing market, and we continue to look for exceptional Wizards who are eager to make a significant impact on our team. At Wiz, you’ll have the freedom to think creatively, dream big, and use your full range of skills to contribute to our momentous growth. Come join our team and help us create secure cloud environments that allow even the best companies to move faster, all while having some fun!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wiz is building something special in the world of events and community experiences, creating strategic engines for engagement, learning, and brand impact.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;We value excellence and impeccable execution at every touchpoint, and we are looking for a highly organized &lt;strong&gt;Events Program Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to own the end-to-end content journey of our Wiz-led events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will serve as the bridge between marketing, product, speakers, and design teams to ensure every piece of content—from registration campaigns to session narratives and on-stage presentations—is compelling, aligned, and delivered with excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Content Strategy &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define messaging frameworks for event registration campaigns, emails, landing pages, and attendee journeys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Marketing to develop consistent, on-brand campaign content that drives registrations and engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure content quality and alignment across all attendee-facing touchpoints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Session &amp;amp; Speaker Content Ownership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the full session content lifecycle - from call-for-abstracts to final presentation delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work directly with internal and external speakers to refine session titles, abstracts, and narratives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide speakers on structure, messaging, and brand alignment to raise session impact and quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate review cycles, deadlines, approvals, and compliance with event goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration &amp;amp; Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the go-to for content timelines, stakeholder updates, and content deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with design, production, and marketing operations to ensure flawless execution&lt;/li&gt;
